..TEXT:
Nino de' Visconti of Pisa, nephew of Count
Ugolino, and Judge of Gallura in Sardinia.  Dante had known him
at the siege of Caprona, in 1290, where he saw the frightened
garrison march out under safeguard.  ^Inf.~ XXI. 95.  It was this
"gentle Judge," who hanged Friar Gomita for peculation. ^Inf.~
XXII. 82.
