..TEXT:
The arms of Gallura.  "According to Fara, a writer
of the sixteenth century," says Valery, ^Voyage en Corse et en
Sardaigne~, II. 37, "the elegant but somewhat chimerical
historian of Sardinia, Gallura is a Gallic colony; its arms are a
cock; and one might find some analogy between the natural
vivacity of its inhabitants and that of the French."  Nino thinks
it would look better on a tombstone than a viper.
