..TEXT:
In the original ^al sommo smalto~, to the highest
enamel; referring either to the Terrestrial Paradise, enamelled
with flowers, or to the highest heaven enamelled with stars.  The
azure-stone, ^pierre d'azur~, or lapis lazuli, is perhaps a fair
equivalent for the ^smalto~, particularly if the reference be to
the sky.
