..TEXT:
With this canto ends the first day in Purgatory,
as indicated by the description of evening at the beginning, and
the rising of the stars in line 89.  With it closes also the
first subdivision of this part of the poem, indicated, as the
reader will not fail to notice, by the elaborate introduction of
the next canto.
